    },
    {
      "id": "47e8e150b3bba6d7bc5cd10873d33e82c4404c71",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-16 21:25:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI am not sure what to make of this failure.  Are you seeing these ldiskfs failures anywhere else?\n\nI suppose it is possible that I'm not misconfiguring ldiskfs and tripping this bug, but I can't see where the misconfiguration would be yet.  I thought this patch would be a no-op.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "957893bb73a2b28dc59ab2d8bfd40774b24af1fc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-16 22:42:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nAh, I think I understand the problem here.  The Lustre code is including ldiskfs/ldiskfs/ldiskfs.h, and there is one dependency on CONFIG_LDISKFS_FS_XATTR for a field in struct ldiskfs_inode_info.  If this is not set, then the xattr_sem is missing, and the osd-ldiskfs code will be accessing/modifying fields in this structure incorrectly.\n\nIt is probably easiet to keep the CONFIG_LDISKFS_FS_XATTR in lustre-build-ldiskfs.m4 for now.  The conditional check (which is always true for ldiskfs and every vendor kernel) has been removed in the 3.7 kernel already.  Probably worth a comment that this should be removed after 3.7, or earlier if the supported vendor kernels backport the removal of this CONFIG option.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7559ee9cb3d76fe0f26a2e4cc84fd8888ff89165",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-16 22:51:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAhh, thanks alot Andreas!  I'll look around more carefully for other things like that, that \"git grep\" won't turn up.\n\nI think it would be nice if ldiskfs set a define in some header used by lustre so this can't happen.  I'll look into doing something like that...might just go with your suggestion in the short term though.  At the least I'll document why it is still needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "aa5fbddced848d3b9d802c507f3e5f614e5ccfc6",
      "author": {
