    {
      "id": "09a6505574e44059ccdde7735941ab8834bb3938",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-18 12:49:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nSeems like a lot of complexity for a single option (CONFIG_LDISKFS_FS_XATTR) which is already removed in 3.7.  \n\nThere were no other CONFIG_EXT4 options in the ext4.h header.  If anything, I'd rather just modify the ldiskfs.h header, since we know it will be included everywhere, rather than have a fragile patch that will silently break if some new file is not patched to add the include.\n\nThat said, I'd rather just keep the one line as-is, or hard code it into some file for the remaining time it needs to live.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "1b1e020b295af0408684847f19cd3e1e67004f63",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-18 22:47:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nGranted this functionality obviously isn't needed at this moment in time.  But we've needed it several times in the past, and rather than doing it \"right\" folks took the easy way out and intertwined the build systems of lustre and ldiskfs.\n\nBut if you want to leave that for a future date when it is really needed, I have no argument.  I'll update with the simple fix.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
