      },
      "date": "2013-03-11 16:14:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nWhile working on patches for LU-1812 I figured out a easier way to expose ldiskfs configurations to osd-ldiskfs. The idea is to create two config headers.\n\nAC_CONFIG_HEADERS([config.h ldiskfs_config.h])\n\nWith a new file ldiskfs_config.h.incontaining only the variables that osd-ldiskfs is interested in. I like to push this new approach if that is okay with you.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "369f5ef7db7fdd80fa0d71db63cda37b5fb84a3c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-11 18:00:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nJames, if you look at revision 2 of this change, you'll see that I tried something similar with a lustre_definitions.h.in.  Andreas didn't like it for complexity and lack of current real use case.  If you figured out a way to use the more built-in functionality of AC_CONFIG_HEADERS, that is great!  I would back that.  I am not familiar with that functionality, so I look forward to seeing your patch.\n\nI'd say just start it with a change new change id in gerrit.  I have no problem abandoning my change if yours works out.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
