        "subject": "LU-1199 build: Cleanup ldiskfs kernel config defines",
        "message": "LU-1199 build: Cleanup ldiskfs kernel config defines\n\nMake it more clear what the purpose of the \"CONFIG_LDISKFS_*\"\ndefines are with a comment, and separate them from options\nthat do not necessarily originate in the kernel source. Also,\nremove these settings from Lustre's build file, since Lustre\ndoes not (directly) use them.\n\nHowever, Lustre does use ldiskfs headers.  One of these options,\nCONFIG_EXT4_FS_XATTR, is set explicitly by a new ldiskfs patch\nso that the value is not undefined when Lustre includes the\nheader.\n\nChange-Id: I5c35f26ff7cb7dd59a6ab431c965980186acc60a\nSigned-off-by: Christopher J. Morrone <morrone2@llnl.gov>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
